appears to load generated bytecode discovered after the native executable is built, which could make the catch acceptable. I want to make sure I'm fully understanding this process.\\\\n\\\\n**Evaluating script errors**\\\\n\\\\nI'm noticing the script is generating an error related to both resource and reflection. It involves dynamic compilation, which isn't supported, but that's acceptable since the test needs to generate helper bytecode. On a native level, it will catch errors before resource calls, which means those call sites aren't covered in native but are in the Java agent. I might need to ensure all top-level tests are public. That seems okay!\\\", \\\"thinkingSignature\\\": \\\"{\\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"rs_0a6e7474391d17770169f5a6f008f48194821ba0e024cbb0b6\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"reasoning\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"encrypted_content\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"gAAAAABp9acOi17iN0RyF8vVAg-elgpZZGI2sHg1Y-KHgsgQ413woS-APgky5Q0i7cSbGr4YoUc4TapBqQpmiWo4_7nSwq1cN4k6GAuWefeGPwqf-dvxLDwNw7CcuAJaEIcXRPmsSMRXYdxWA8-rdWh_IFC75e_VaAqlkINiO1CfgWkHrpzgHSjzhWsDkb9_ECO6emCawmNFiOdjObRxf86prcog6JZvrw4DP__wcuSOHgpQW7NLPHdHYwdJ2W36oaCiCYaJdaNoydphpuyEdbMsNLhKhLeYgR6IXPXpPedCKMtUAVbIvckZ6UZXUTelwQLRw4mPedbtI2u4JRg1TUssH9amcYHbh4DBjIBb2qZzC0NSTBzgXpHKWigogsbOLdOYWvQEr6ouztnk-ZAulvb238Qi17Ho_mcgCBvia-bxUN6TNdE4I1_JT8SUODILOYbkIUmUTGvoZTUTX86L9YXDS6ummAYgWsqSnO_A6-2zIZnVdAhsURY8jozaVgcTeq3Ua_JxDEzZ_mfYSBmy3SdNUV_j7QlCKn0mpTJZc8gsuHT8ETTewxlJUQohnfs_HfcaRhm_8tiLtxy6n8GziL-T45QPwnQ9PeskAFLWwcsllEBxRygiHulNCtzb49knslNyr0GHbRh0vtwo6i_kWi7I_YqqAW7STh2MyJ21JAi5X2ECYW1J4A3HEvBrfR0EQr65d25uf8wZICyeJ1nMJ_mpemsuOLz5eXD3j06xRwOkyWM78pNol5OrOs02jTL0vLrmP5ZwJVPd2yl26BMnSBJhApoz993w6ezvPKeRHJ_b1wRRbuuS3ckC5V2hsqkMaKh62hIYo0-E8z1a76EZzGBpU6hY_CvS-qC4BvNNQixrrPx7F2_FI9xfgzAWY-iu2OlZi0dhjMaxg5HuOtL1I-2h1eifyhorvIcg0ebd8GZ3Sox3hsNOMN4X8JEvFEpg4A2JAbALhro0w09HfOeUUvoT53zD3JEvUPBn-DKrTeCaicXMvj_RA5mx9pvZFW0BXq7L7iGKVNjHPrRTi_4yeN-WeWE3R4QDMOk0w1pNmoLeEYMSHnOnDnWjDJgN3qPwWsjShgbljqcyAQisbwzHMi5QyjlOakIEQd4Bl